    "long_instructions": "### Layering Multiple Backtracks with Loops\r\n\r\nSometimes you may want to play sounds together that have different lengths. You can wrap a `play together` block around multiple loops of varying lengths. \r\n\r\n**Do this:** \r\n- Find at least one drum beat, bass sound, lead sound, and vocal sound. \r\n- Find two sounds that are the same length and put them in the looping `play together` block.\r\n- Change the amount of times each loops so they last at least 12 measures and start and end at the same time. \r\n ",
